@startuml 5B_Module_Toggles
title 5-B · Feature Flag & Module Access Toggles (UC-P14 to UC-P17)

start
|Service Admin (Super Admin/Ops)|
:Open Feature Flag Management;
if (Admin action?) then (Create Flag)
  :Enter flag key, description and default value;
  |System|
  :Validate unique flag key;
  :Create FeatureFlag record;
elseif (Admin action?) then (Enable For Tenant)
  :Select flag and tenant;
  |System|
  :Create or update TenantFeatureOverride\nis_enabled = true;
elseif (Admin action?) then (Disable For Tenant)
  :Select flag and tenant;
  |System|
  :Create or update TenantFeatureOverride\nis_enabled = false;
else (Rollout Globally)
  :Select flag and global value;
  |System|
  :Update global rollout state;
endif

|System|
:Write audit log for feature change;
:FeatureFlagManagementService.evaluateFlag()\nreturns value by global default + tenant override;

|Tenant Admin / Fan|
:Request module or API protected by feature flag;

|System|
:Run EnforceFeatureFlag middleware;
if (Feature enabled for tenant?) then (Yes)
  :Allow module access;
else (No)
  :Hide module or return 403/upgrade prompt;
endif

stop
@enduml
